      • getPath

        public java.lang.String getPath(Script script)
        Returns the path for the script.

        The path describes where the script fits in the storyworld. If you need to work with the path decomposition use #getScriptLocators() instead. This method is just the concatenation of path component names with the separator ": ".

      • getScriptLocators

        public java.lang.String[] getScriptLocators(Script script)
        Returns the script strings that indicate where the script is placed in the storyworld. The strings alone do not suffice for that, but together with the script type they do.

        This method is a convenient to avoid parsing the script path when the locators are needed.

      • getPathComponents

        public java.lang.String[] getPathComponents(Script script)
        Returns the path components.

        This method is a convenient to avoid parsing the script path when it need to be edited in some special way.

      • containsUndefinedOperators

        public static boolean containsUndefinedOperators(Script s)
        Returns:
        true iff the script contains undefined operators.

      • sniff

        public java.lang.String sniff(Script script)
        Returns:
        null if all the script nodes have valid operators, otherwise it returns an error string.

      • sniffNode

        public java.lang.String sniffNode(Script script,
                                  Script.Node zNode)
        Returns:
        null if all the nodes in the subtree rooted at a given node have valid operators, otherwise it returns an error string.

      • isValid

        public java.lang.String isValid(Script script,
                                Operator op,
                                Script.Node zNode)
        Returns an error string if the operator is not valid for a given node in the script. Returns null if the operator is valid.

        This code is intended to be used for sniffing as well as for selecting the correct operators to offer when editing a script.

      • getValidOperators

        Returns the valid operators of a menu for a given node of the script.
